Earlier in the year, about a month before the Commissary had commenced his Visitation of the Archdeaconry of Uornwall, an ex- traordinary attempt to deceive the Archbishop was made by a pro- minent layman of that County, which can only be regarded as fraudulent. The offender, evidently, thought that, in the remote locality in which he lived, he might safely take advantage of the fact that the authority of the Diocesan Bishop had been, for a time, suspended, and that the Archbishop‘s Cominissary and his officers were strangers in that land.
